ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_axpre-ltirr | |- ( A e. RR -> -. A <RR A ) |
| 2 |  | #P_ltxrlt | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ A e. RR ) -> ( A < A <-> A <RR A ) ) |
| 3 | 2 | #P_anidms | |- ( A e. RR -> ( A < A <-> A <RR A ) ) |
| 4 | 1, 3 | #P_mtbird | |- ( A e. RR -> -. A < A ) |
\
 Real number less-than is irreflexive.  Axiom for real and complex numbers, derived from set theory.  This restates ~ ax-pre-ltirr with ordering on the extended reals.  New proofs should use ~ ltnr instead for naming consistency.  (New usage is discouraged.)  (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 15-Jan-2020.)
